"title": "8150: revival, personal",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8150: revival, personal",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The bringing back of individuals to life or vigour both at the point of personal regeneration through the work of the Holy Spirit and at other times in believers' lives.</p>\n<h2>Aspects of individual revival</h2>\n<h3>Physical revival</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:16\">ISA 38:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:18-Judg15:19\">JDG 15:18–15:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:27\">1SA 14:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam30:11-1Sam30:12\">1SA 30:11–30:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:7-1Kgs19:8\">1KI 19:7–19:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:25\">JOB 33:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps41:3\">PSA 41:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps116:8-Ps116:9\">PSA 116:8–116:9</a></p>\n<h3>Revival of hope</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:27\">GEN 45:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:14-Ruth4:15\">RUT 4:14–4:15</a></p>\n<h3>Revival of sanity</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:26\">DAN 4:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:34\">DAN 4:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:36\">DAN 4:36</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual revival</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:3\">PSA 23:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:9-1Kgs19:15\">1KI 19:9–19:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:15-John21:19\">JHN 21:15–21:19</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit brings regeneration by giving spiritual life to those dead in sin</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:1-Eph2:5\">EPH 2:1–2:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:5-Titus3:6\">TIT 3:5–3:6</a></p>\n<h2>Preparation for personal spiritual revival</h2>\n<h3>The Holy Spirit convicts</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:8-John16:11\">JHN 16:8–16:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:37\">ACT 2:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:5\">1TH 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>Individuals appeal to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:14\">JER 17:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:7-Ps51:12\">PSA 51:7–51:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:34-Ps119:37\">PSA 119:34–119:37</a></p>\n<h3>Individuals long for God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:1-Ps42:2\">PSA 42:1–42:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps63:1\">PSA 63:1</a></p>\n<h3>Personal repentance is required</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:1-Ps51:4\">PSA 51:1–51:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:26\">2CH 32:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:11-2Chr33:13\">2CH 33:11–33:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job22:23\">JOB 22:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:19\">JER 15:19</a></p>\n<h2>The believer must take responsibility for personal revival</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:6\">2TI 1:6</a></strong></p>\n<h2>God is active in bringing about personal revival</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:15\">ISA 57:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps43:3-Ps43:4\">PSA 43:3–43:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:31\">ISA 40:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:14\">HAG 1:14</a></p>\n<h3>God's law may initiate personal revival</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:7\">PSA 19:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:130\">PSA 119:130</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:162\">PSA 119:162</a></p>\n<h2>The fruit of personal revival</h2>\n<h3>God receives praise</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:3\">PSA 40:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:50\">2SA 22:50</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:49\">PSA 18:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:15\">PSA 51:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps59:16\">PSA 59:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps61:8\">PSA 61:8</a></p>\n<h3>God is obeyed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:15-2Chr33:16\">2CH 33:15–33:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:14\">ACT 2:14</a> <em>Peter had denied Jesus Christ seven weeks before.</em></p>",
